      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Reality systems are designed based on individual
customer requirements. Customized systems require customized services.
Reality services makes it easier for you to operate, install and maintain
your system. There are two types of service offers:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On demand services:</b> Offers a range of services at a
pre-determined cost or hourly rate.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Service contracts:</b> Offers customizable services agreements
to meet your specific needs, with a yearly fee and pre-agreed upon
rates. This makes it easier for proactive budgeting and service planning.</p>
                     <note class="- topic/note ">A service contract is a formal, mutually-agreed-upon, binding
contract between Schneider Electric and a client. In the contract,
we make a commitment to provide services over a fixed time period,
and at fixed rates or a yearly fee.</note>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
